# Admin Dashboard & Notifications Complete!

I have fully implemented the Admin Dashboard and the In-App Notification system for the web platform, while keeping the mobile platform safely intact.

## What Was Accomplished

### 1. Database & Backend Engine
- Added the `ADMIN` user role.
- Updated the User model to track `lastActiveAt`. This timestamp automatically updates behind the scenes when a user uses the app, allowing us to accurately track who is "Online".
- Created the `Notification` database model to store messages sent to users' accounts.
- Built the new API endpoints (`/api/v1/admin/*` and `/api/v1/notifications/*`) and secured them so that only an `ADMIN` can access the admin dashboard.

### 2. The Web Admin Dashboard
- **Location:** It is accessible via `/admin`.
- **Restricted Access:** The "Admin Dashboard" button only appears in the sidebar for users with the `ADMIN` role. If a non-admin tries to navigate there directly, they are redirected away.
- **Features:** 
  - Real-time stats showing Total Users and Online Users.
  - A clean table listing all registered users with their roles and online status.
  - A notification form where you can type announcements and choose to send them via **Emails**, **In-App**, or **Both**.

### 3. User Notification Bell
- Added a `NotificationBell` to the top-left header of the sidebar for all users.
- It displays a red badge indicating the number of unread announcements.
- Clicking the bell opens a dropdown showing the notifications, and clicking the checkmark marks them as read!

---

## Next Steps: Promoting Your Account

To access the new dashboard, you need to promote your personal account to an `ADMIN`.

I created a script to do this safely without you having to touch the raw database.

**Run this command in your terminal (make sure to use your actual email):**

```bash
cd "nedai-server"
npm run make-admin your.email@example.com
```

Once the terminal confirms you've been promoted, log back into your account on the web platform, and you will see the **Admin Dashboard** button appear at the bottom of the sidebar!
